    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-22T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="1538"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/63a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Canova</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-22T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Proceed to Zacatecas and exert every energy to secure full information especially
                    regarding reported death of two French priests and imprisonment of eleven others
                    and generally regarding treatment accorded to representatives of all religious
                    orders. Telegraph results. Forward mail description conditions since the attack
                    on and fall of Zacatecas, covering treatment accorded foreigners and their
                    interests.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
